Reasoning: The paper deals with activity and event recognition using neural networks and multi-modal cues such as RGB image, optical flow, and acoustic signal. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. The use of neural networks also suggests that the paper may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) in the context of event recognition, which suggests that it may also belong to the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
